result.execSummary:
The defendant Jacob Mcghee was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Possession of THC (2nd+ Offense), a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(3g)(e).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Defendant Jacob Mcghee in court with attorney Tina M. Abernethy-Mays.  Defendant Jacob Mcghee in custody.  Galen Bayne-Allison appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Court calls 15CF246, 15CF148 and 13CF132 @ 10:26 a.m. Agreement stated - 13CF132 State will withdraw motion to revoke DEJ, will be extended with same conditions. 15CF148 Def will  plead ct 1, cts 2 & 3 dismiss and read in. Ct 1 - time served, costs. 15CF246, Def will waive prelim, plead to cts 1 & 2, DRI cts 3 & 4. Ct 1 costs, ct 2 withheld sentence, 2 yrs probation, concurrent with probation currently serving, conditions explained.  Atty Abernethy-Mays and Def agree. 15CF246 waiver of prelim filed. Court reviews with Def. Court finds waiver knowing and voluntary. Probable cause found and bind over. Information filed, copy received, reading waived. 13CF132 amended DEJ filed. State withdraws original agreement and motion to revoke, asks Court to approve amended agreement. State has complied with VWNR. Court reviews agreement, approves and signs. 15CF148 State asks Court forfeit bond being held. Response by Atty Abernethy-Mays. State will withdraw request. Plea quest. reviewed. 15CF148 ct 1 - no contest plea. 15CF246 cts 1 & 2 - no contest pleas. 15CF148 cts 2 & 3 dismissed and read in. 15CF246 cts 3 & 4 dismissed and read in. Constitutional rights, elements, possible penalties reviewed. Atty Abernethy-Mays satisfied. Court finds Def understands and pleas freely & voluntarily made. Factual basis. Court accepts pleas and finds guilty of 15CF148 ct 1 possess THC 2nd or subsq. and 15CF246 ct 1 possess drg para as repeater and ct 2 felony bail jumping as repeater. Sentencing remarks by Counsel. Nothing by Defendant. Remarks by the Court. Court will follow agreement. 15CF148 ct 1 - 176 days jail w/credit for 176 days, sentence complete, court costs, DNA surcharge, apply bond, pmt plan for balance. First pmt due in Oct. 15CF246 ct 1 - court costs, DNA surcharge, pmt plan. Ct 2- sentence withheld, 2 yrs probation, court costs, DNA surcharge, DNA sample if not already taken. No credit if revoked. Def advised of firearms and voting restrictions.   If probation is revoked or discharged with outstanding financial obligations, a civil judgment shall be entered, without further order of the court, against the defendant in favor of restitution victims and/or governmental entities for the balance due.  All available enforcement actions will be used to collect the debt. Postconviction rights. Def asks probation be transferred to Eau Claire. Court does not object, however, up to dept.
Status conference on May 26, 2016 at 09:30 am.
Bail/Bond Forfeiture Hearing on May 26, 2016 at 09:30 am.
